  "status": "Stagnant",
  "summary": "The proposed standard defines a lightweight interface to expose functional ownership and balances of held tokens. A held token is a token owned by a contract. This standard may be implemented by smart contracts which hold [EIP-20](./eip-20.md), [EIP-721](./eip-721.md), or [EIP-1155](./eip-1155.md) tokens and is intended to be consumed by both on-chain and off-chain systems that rely on ownership and balance verification.",
  "title": "Held token interface"
